<div class="wp-block-yoast-seo-table-of-contents yoast-table-of-contents"><h2 id="table-of-contents">Table of Contents</h2><ul><li><a href="#h-salad-ingredients">Salad Ingredients</a></li><li><a href="#h-how-to-make-cucumber-watermelon-salad">How to Make Cucumber Watermelon Salad</a></li><li><a href="#h-what-to-serve-with-cucumber-watermelon-salad">What to Serve with Cucumber Watermelon Salad</a></li><li><a href="#h-salad-faqs">Salad FAQs</a></li><li><a href="#h-storage-instructions">Storage Instructions</a></li><li><a href="#wprm-recipe-container-75024">Balsamic Watermelon Cucumber Salad Recipe</a></li><li><a href="#h-more-summer-salad-recipes-nbsp">More Summer Salad Recipes:&nbsp;</a></li></ul></div>


<p>This watermelon and cucumber salad&nbsp;is a spinoff of a salad I love to eat at one of my favorite Puerto Vallarta beach bars. <strong>It&rsquo;s refreshing, light, and the combination of all the flavors is just perfection.</strong></p>



<p>There&rsquo;s juicy sweet watermelon, cucumber, strong and peppery arugula, tanginess from goat cheese, crunchy candied nuts, and a homemade balsamic glaze. </p>



<p><strong>If you&rsquo;ve never thought that watermelon can be delicious in a more savory application, think again because this salad will just knock your socks off.</strong></p>



<p>It&rsquo;s so fresh and perfect for hot summer days.</p>



<span id="more-74999"></span>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="650" height="975" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/balsamic-watermelon-and-cucumber-salad/?tp_image_id=77710" data-pin-title="Balsamic Watermelon and Cucumber Salad" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20650%20975'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Balsamic Watermelon Cucumber Salad &mdash; An EASY, healthy, and light salad with watermelon, cucumber, arugula, goat cheese, candied nuts, and drizzled with a homemade balsamic glaze!! A PERFECT summer salad for those days when it's too hot to cook!!" class="wp-image-77710" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3.jpg 650w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-240x360.jpg 240w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-480x720.jpg 480w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-280x420.jpg 280w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-560x840.jpg 560w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-360x540.jpg 360w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" data-lazy-src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="650" height="975" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/balsamic-watermelon-and-cucumber-salad/?tp_image_id=77710" data-pin-title="Balsamic Watermelon and Cucumber Salad" src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3.jpg" alt="Balsamic Watermelon Cucumber Salad &mdash; An EASY, healthy, and light salad with watermelon, cucumber, arugula, goat cheese, candied nuts, and drizzled with a homemade balsamic glaze!! A PERFECT summer salad for those days when it's too hot to cook!!" class="wp-image-77710" srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3.jpg 650w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-240x360.jpg 240w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-480x720.jpg 480w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-280x420.jpg 280w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-560x840.jpg 560w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-3-360x540.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-salad-ingredients">Salad Ingredients</h2>



<p>You only need a handful of ingredients to make this watermelon and cucumber salad, including:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Balsamic vinegar</li>



<li>Sugar</li>



<li>Watermelon&nbsp;</li>



<li>Cucumber</li>



<li>Arugula</li>



<li>Goat cheese</li>



<li><a href="https://www.averiecooks.com/sweet-with-heat-cinnamon-sugar-candied-nuts/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self">Candied nuts</a> &ndash; store-bought or homemade</li>
</ul>



<p><strong><em>Note</em></strong><em>: Scroll down to the recipe card section of the post for the ingredients with amounts included and for more complete directions.</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter"><img decoding="async" width="650" height="975" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/balsamic-watermelon-and-cucumber-salad/?tp_image_id=77709" data-pin-title="Balsamic Watermelon and Cucumber Salad" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20650%20975'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Balsamic Watermelon Cucumber Salad &mdash; An EASY, healthy, and light salad with watermelon, cucumber, arugula, goat cheese, candied nuts, and drizzled with a homemade balsamic glaze!! A PERFECT summer salad for those days when it's too hot to cook!!" class="wp-image-77709" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2.jpg 650w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-240x360.jpg 240w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-480x720.jpg 480w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-280x420.jpg 280w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-560x840.jpg 560w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-360x540.jpg 360w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" data-lazy-src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="650" height="975" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/balsamic-watermelon-and-cucumber-salad/?tp_image_id=77709" data-pin-title="Balsamic Watermelon and Cucumber Salad" src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2.jpg" alt="Balsamic Watermelon Cucumber Salad &mdash; An EASY, healthy, and light salad with watermelon, cucumber, arugula, goat cheese, candied nuts, and drizzled with a homemade balsamic glaze!! A PERFECT summer salad for those days when it's too hot to cook!!" class="wp-image-77709" srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2.jpg 650w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-240x360.jpg 240w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-480x720.jpg 480w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-280x420.jpg 280w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-560x840.jpg 560w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/watermelonsalad-2-360x540.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-cucumber-watermelon-salad">How to Make Cucumber Watermelon Salad</h2>



<p>This watermelon salad with cucumber is drizzled with a homemade balsamic glaze, which you&rsquo;ll need to make before tossing the salad together. <strong>It&rsquo;s simple!</strong></p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Making the balsamic glaze:</strong> Add the balsamic vinegar and granulated sugar to a large saucepan, bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until the volume has reduced by about 80% and the sauce is thick and syrupy.</li>



<li><strong>Assemble the salad: </strong>To a medium bowl, add all the remaining ingredients, stir to combine, and drizzle as much of the balsamic reduction as desired.</li>
</ol>


