iecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-378x529.jpg 378w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-288x403.jpg 288w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-128x179.jpg 128w" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/black-bean-burgers/?tp_image_id=80386" data-lazy-src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-378x529.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="378" height="529" src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-378x529.jpg" class="attachment-cwp_archive_lg size-cwp_archive_lg" alt="A black bean burger with lettuce, tomato, cheese, red onion, and guacamole." data-pin-nopin="nopin" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 50vw, 276px" srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-378x529.jpg 378w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-288x403.jpg 288w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/blackbeanburgers-10-128x179.jpg 128w" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/black-bean-burgers/?tp_image_id=80386"></noscript></a></div><div class="post-summary__content"><h3 class="post-summary__title" id="black-bean-burgers"><a href="https://www.averiecooks.com/black-bean-burgers/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self">Black Bean Burgers</a></h3></div></article><article class="post-summary"><div class="post-summary__image"><a href="https://www.averiecooks.com/grilled-pork-chops/" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self"><img decoding="async" width="378" height="529" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20378%20529'%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-cwp_archive_lg size-cwp_archive_lg" alt="Grilled Pork Chops on a plate." data-pin-nopin="nopin" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 50vw, 276px" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-378x529.jpg 378w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-288x403.jpg 288w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-128x179.jpg 128w" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/grilled-pork-chops/?tp_image_id=89411" data-lazy-src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-378x529.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="378" height="529" src="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-378x529.jpg" class="attachment-cwp_archive_lg size-cwp_archive_lg" alt="Grilled Pork Chops on a plate." data-pin-nopin="nopin" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 50vw, 276px" srcset="https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-378x529.jpg 378w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-288x403.jpg 288w, https://www.averiecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/grilledporkchops-14-128x179.jpg 128w" data-pin-url="https://www.averiecooks.com/grilled-pork-chops/?tp_image_id=89411"></noscript></a></div><div class="post-summary__content"><h3 class="post-summary__title" id="grilled-pork-chops"><a href="https://www.averiecooks.com/grilled-pork-chops/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self">Grilled Pork Chops</a></h3></div></article></div></section>

<div class="block-faq-title cwp-large"><div class="block-faq-title__inner">

<h2 class="wp-block-heading block-faq-title__title" id="h-salad-faqs">Salad FAQs</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1717749248871"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How Can I adjust the sweetness level of the balsamic glaze? </strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">I used a 500 milliliter (about 17 ounces) bottle of balsamic vinegar and added close to 1 cup sugar. You can start with 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar and taste your sauce when it looks like it&rsquo;s about halfway done, but for me that&rsquo;s not quite sweet enough and it&rsquo;s too intensely vinegary, so I went with closer to 1 cup for this batch.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1717749294707"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I Add a Protein Source to the Salad?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes! I bet <a href="https://www.averiecooks.com/tag/grilled-chicken/" data-wpel-link="internal" target="_self">grilled chicken</a> would pair wonderfully with this cucumber watermelon salad. </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1717749316884"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I Use a store-bought balsamic glaze? </strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Of course! <a data-grocers-list-rewritten="true" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://linksta.io/56bb0b7e/wp" data-grocerslist-rewritten-link="https://linksta.io/56bb0b7e" target="_blank" data-wpel-link="external">Trader Joe&rsquo;s</a> is one I tend to keep on hand for times like this and there are many other brands out there these days if you don&rsquo;t have a Trader Joe&rsquo;s in your area.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1717749374422"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can the goat cheese be omitted or substituted? </strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">As written, this is a naturally vegetarian salad recipe, but you can make it vegan by skipping the goat cheese or using a vegan cheese. <br><br>And if you just don&rsquo;t like goat cheese, try using feta instead! </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1717749436642"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can the salad be made in advance? </strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Not really. The watermelon releases juice quickly and will cause the cucumber and arugula to soften. However, you can prep the individual fruits and veggies and store them in separate containers in the fridge up to 48 hours before tossing the salad. The balsamic glaze can be prepared weeks in advance. </p> </div> </div>

</div></div>


